<li><a href="1997#9january1997">9 January 1997</a></li>
<li><a href="1997#1january1997">1 January 1997</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="18december1997">Update 1152G # Date 18 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 20 - MOBILITY ALLOWANCE - Independent living skills training/MA for high school students. See guidelines 20.650 to 20.692.</p>
<p>Independent living skills or life skills courses can be accepted as vocational training for MA purposes regardless of length of course and likely employment outcomes. Mobility allowance will also be payable to students attending secondary education who meet other MA eligibility criteria.</p>
<h2 id="15december1997">Update 1133G # Date 15 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Provisional payment of newstart allowance pending disability support pension determination. See guideline 12.1000 to 12.1071.</p>
<p>Legislative changes allow persons claiming disability support pension (DSP) to be paid non activity tested newstart allowance or youth training allowance pending determination of their DSP claim.</p>
<h2 id="11december1997">Update 1120G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Rate of payment. See guidelines 17.10820 to 17.10830.</p>
<p>Amend policy regarding family payment following transfer of child related payments for Department of Veterans Affairs.</p>
<h2>Update 1119G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Residence and overseas absences. See guidelines 17.5000 to 17.5200.</p>
<p>Currently family payment is restricted to the minimum family payment rate after a customer has been overseas for more than 13 weeks and immediately when a child leaves Australia. From 1 January 1998, family payment will be restricted to the minimum rate after a customer and/or their child/ren have been overseas for more than 13 weeks.</p>
<h2>Update 1118G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 41N - PARENTING ALLOWANCE - Newly arrived residents waiting period. See guidelines 41N.3810 to 41N.3814.</p>
<p>Family members (including partners) of Australian citizens and long term Australian residents are exempt from the two year newly arrived residents waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 1117G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 41N - PARENTING ALLOWANCE - Partial debt waiver on transfer between pension and parenting allowance. See guidelines 41N.7590 to 41N.7594.</p>
<p>Where overpayment arises in parenting allowance pension transfers, one week's worth of payment may be waived in some cases.</p>
<h2>Update 1116G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 26 - EMPLOYMENT AND EDUCATION PAYMENTS - Widow allowance added to PART H heading. See guidelines 26.7000 to 26.7800.</p>
<p>Added widow allowance to qualifying payments for pensioner education supplement.</p>
<h2>Update 1115G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Basic qualifications changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.16100 to 12.17301.</p>
<p>Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service (CES) and social security where jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable.</p>
<h2>Update 1114G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Away from home rate. See guidelines 45.11200 to 45.11202.</p>
<p>The away from home rate of youth training allowance is payable if a person is approved by Centrelink as needing to live away from home to undertake job search, education, training or other employment preparation activity.</p>
<h2>Update 1113G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 46 - WIDOW ALLOWANCE - Annual review - general &amp; selection of customers. See guidelines 46.3100 to 46.3129 (deleted).</p>
<p>Deleting reference to widow allowance annual reviews - they no longer exist.</p>
<h2>Update 1112G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Basic qualifications changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and Jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.13000 to 12.13503 (Guidelines 12.13900 to 13940 have been deleted).</p>
<p>Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service (CES) and social security where jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable. Addition of policy advice concerning changes to abridged/reclaim policy.</p>
<h2>Update 1111G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Basic qualifications changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.8400 to 12.8403.</p>
<p>Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service (CES) and social security where jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable.</p>
<h2>Update 1110G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Suitable work. See guidelines 12.2110 to 12.2119.</p>
<p>Work may be declared unsuitable for a customer on the basis of moral, cultural or religious grounds. While this was previously possible, it is now explicitly stated that such grounds may be valid.</p>
<h2>Update 1109G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - (1) Issue of Employer Contact Certificates (ECC's). (2) Basic qualifications changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and Jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.2815 to 12.2829.</p>
<p>(1) Clarified guidelines on issue of Employer Contact Certificates.</p>
<p>(2) Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service (CES) and social security where jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable. Addition of policy advice concerning changes to reduced reporting.</p>
<h2>Update 1108G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 33 - SUPERANNUATION, ANNUITIES AND ALLOCATED PRODUCTS - Income and assets treatment of superannuation products. See guidelines 33.000 to 33.6360.</p>
<p>A major re-write of Chapter 33 which expands on current policy and will produce different outcomes in the assessment of superannuation products. Additional instructions have been inserted to take account of recent policy changes. Changes reflect changes in policy announced in previous budgets.</p>
<h2>Update 1107G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Basic Qualifications Changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.15100 to 12.15647.</p>
<p>Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service and social security where Jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable. Addition of policy advice concerning and changes to reduced reporting.</p>
<h2>Update 1105G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 35 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Parental income and assets test. Guidelines 35.1320 to 35.1323 have been deleted.</p>
<p>The parental income test for allowance customers under 18 years of age is based on taxable family income and the number of dependent children in the family. For newstart allowance a dependent child under 22 years of age attracts an additional free area. While for youth training allowance and sickness allowance a dependent child under 23 years of age attracts an additional free area.</p>
<h2>Update 1104G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Parental income and assets test. See guidelines 45.18300 to 45.18302.</p>
<p>The minimum rate of allowance for newstart allowance, youth training allowance, sickness allowance and special benefit customers under 18 years of age and subject to the parental means test was abolished on 23 January 1997.</p>
<h2>Update 1103G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Form SU19 must be date stamped. See guidelines 45.15000 to 45.15009.</p>
<p>SU19s need to be date stamped on receipt as date of lodgement is required for such purposes as debt recovery. Guidelines 45.15002 and 45.15006 have been amalgamated as essentially they say the same thing.</p>
<h2>Update 1102G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Education leavers waiting period. See guideline 45.7600 to 45.7603.</p>
<p>The education leavers waiting period cut-off date for secondary school leavers is 15 February - see s100(6), SYAA.</p>
<h2>Update 1101G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Australian Taxation Office (ATO) liaisons - family payment. Guidelines 17.11600 to 17.11791 have been deleted.</p>
<p>Amendment removes reference to these procedures, as direct liaison with the Australian Taxation Office to verify income has ceased.</p>
<h2>Update 1100G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Payment of youth training allowance while sick. See guidelines 45.1000 to 45.1062.</p>
<p>From 20 March 1996 legislative changes were introduced that amended the rules for incapacitated youth training allowance and sickness allowance. Unemployed customers on allowance who are temporarily incapacitated for more than 13 weeks due to illness or injury, no longer have to transfer to sickness allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 1099G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART ALLOWANCE - Minimum rate of payment for customers subject to the parental means test was abolished in January 1997. See guidelines 12.18300 to 12.18302.</p>
<p>The minimum rate of allowance for newstart allowance, youth training allowance, sickness allowance and special benefit customers under 18 years of age and subject to the parental means test was abolished on 23 January 1997.</p>
<h2>Update 1098G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART ALLOWANCE - Work for the dole. See guidelines 12.15600 to 12.15607.</p>
<p>This amendment is to delete 'jobsearch allowance'.</p>
<h2>Update 1097G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 38 - CHILD SUPPORT - Exemptions from maintenance action. See guidelines 38.2560 to 38.2577.</p>
<p>Aboriginal &amp; Islander Liaison Officers, rather than social workers, will generally make recommendations for exemptions from maintenance action for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander customers on the basis of cultural considerations.</p>
<h2>Update 1096G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Payments from an employer. See guidelines 14.2610 to 14.2611.</p>
<p>National instruction CB970174 erroneously advised network staff that the income maintenance period did not apply to sickness allowance. For sickness allowance, payments from an employer, except for sick leave, are assessed under the income maintenance period rules. Payments of sick leave are assessed in accordance with guidelines 14.2600 to 14.2606.</p>
<h2>Update 1095G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Basic qualification changes to wording in general due to implementation of Centrelink and jobseeker registration. See guidelines 12.7610 to 12.7712.</p>
<p>Changes to all references to Commonwealth Employment Service (CES) and Social Security where jobseeker registration and Centrelink are now applicable.</p>
<h2>Update 1094G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Income verification. See guidelines 17.11000 to 17.11103.</p>
<p>Arrangements for direct verification of income for family payment purposes with the Australian Taxation Office have ceased. Customers who do not have their Taxation Notice of Assessment should contact the ATO directly. The amendment also notes that income details provided by a customer must be given in writing.</p>
<h2>Update 1093G # Date 11 December 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 35 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Historical rates of payment - family payment income and assets limits/maintenance income test. See guidelines 35.4410 to 35.4420.</p>
