<h2>Update 1045G # Date 13 November 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Family payment for under age partner. See guidelines 17.1400 to 17.1403.</p>
<p>This amendment clarifies the legal basis for rejecting claims for family payment made in respect of a partner who is under the age of 16. Whilst the Act might seem to allow payment in such cases, established rules of statutory interpretation allow the claim to be rejected on the basis that to allow the claimant to gain a benefit from their illegal marriage-like relationship would be contrary to public policy.</p>
<h2 id="30october1997">Update 1044G # Date 30 October 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 30 - INCOME: ASSESSMENT FROM FINANCIAL ASSETS - Reduction in deeming rates for financial investments. See guidelines 30.1100 to 30.1403.</p>
<p>From 20 September 1997, extended deeming rates have reduced to 3% and 5%, resulting in an increase in payments to some customers. Note also a change in the financial investment status of superannuation and rollover funds.</p>
