<h2 id="20october1997">Update 1027G # Date 20 October 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Expansion of temporary activity test exemptions in special circumstances, including expectant mothers. See guidelines 12.2700 to 12.2760.</p>
<p>Expectant mothers are now able to obtain an activity test exemption from 6 weeks prior to the expected date of confinement until 6 weeks after the birth of the child. The 13 week legislative restriction on special circumstances exemptions has also been lifted but will only apply to customers in three specified circumstances - jury duty, refugees undertaking a preparatory Adult Migrant English Program course, or customers with temporary caring responsibilities.</p>
<h2 id="16october1997">Update 1033G # Date 16 October 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - (1) Special benefit changes for expectant mothers. See guidelines (1) 15.2600 to 15.2609 and (2) 15.2700 to 15.2705.</p>
<p>(1) Due to activity test changes for newstart and youth training allowance the need for special benefit (SpB) to be paid to pregnant women is significantly reduced. SpB may be paid from six weeks before the expected date of birth to six weeks after the birth. Previously SpB was payable up to 12 weeks before the expected date of birth.</p>
<p>(2) People with temporary caring responsibilities may be eligible for an activity test exemption for newstart allowance or youth training allowance and therefore do not need to be transferred to SpB.</p>
<h2>Update 1032G # Date 16 October 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Determining activity test breaches and application of new activity test penalty periods. See guidelines 12.3000 to 12.3009.</p>
<p>New legislation references and calculation information for new activity test breach penalty periods.</p>
<h2>Update 1031G # Date 16 October 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 20 - MOBILITY ALLOWANCE - Vocational training. See guidelines 20.650 to 20.700.</p>
<p>Before training can be accepted as being vocational training, minimum requirements must be met. These include the objective of the training, the person's intention to undertake gainful employment and the person's ability to undertake gainful employment.</p>
