<h2 id="26june1997">Update 949G # Date 26 June 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 5 - AGE PENSION - Changes to residency qualifications. See guidelines 5.020 to 5.025 and 5.1000 to 5.1004.</p>
<p>From 20 March 1997 a person is qualified for an age pension if the person has reached age pension age and any of the following applies:</p>
<ul><li>The person has ten years qualifying Australian residence.</li>
<li>The person has a qualifying residence exemption for an age pension.</li>
<li>The person was receiving a widow B pension, a widow allowance, a mature age allowance or a partner allowance, immediately before reaching that age;</li>
<li>If the person reached age pension age before 20 March 1997 - the person was receiving a widow B pension, a widow allowance or a partner allowance, immediately before 20 March 1997.</li>
</ul><p>A woman is qualified for an age pension if:</p>
<p>a) the woman has reached age pension age; and</p>
<p>b) the woman's partner has died; and</p>
<p>c) both the woman and her partner were Australian residents when her partner died; and</p>
<p>d) the woman was an Australian resident for a continuous period of at least 104 weeks immediately before the day she lodged the claim for the age pension.</p>
<h2>Update 948G # Date 26 June 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 11 - WIDOW B PENSION - See guidelines 11.000 to 11.3107.</p>
<p>From 20 March 1997 there are no new grants of widow B pension. Current cases remain eligible unless otherwise disqualified. Suspension rather than cancellation should be used for periods of short term earnings.</p>
<p>From 20 March 1997 there is no longer an age pension residency requirement for people who are receiving widow B pension immediately before they turn age pension age, or who are over age pension age. As widow B pensioners reach the women's age pension age they are automatically transferred to age pension from the following pension payday without having to lodge a claim. Widow B pensioners paid under an international agreement or overseas or in receipt of ongoing compensation payments are not transferred to age pension.</p>
<h2>Update 947G # Date 26 June 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 7 - WIFE PENSION - Other possible pension entitlements. See guidelines 7.2500 to 7.2501.</p>
<p>The amendment deletes a note about exploring eligibility for widow B pension. There are no new grants of widow B pension from 20 March 1997.</p>
<h2>Update 946G # Date 26 June 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Timing of payments. See guidelines 2.2110 to 2.2114</p>
<p>The amendments update and simplify procedures to be followed when a pensioner entitlement review form is not returned or returned unclaimed or whereabouts unknown.</p>
