<h2 id="12june1997">Update 943G # Date 12 June 1997</h2>
<p>Chapter 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Casual Employment. See guidelines 45.220 to 45.225.</p>
<p>The period beyond which youth training allowance is cancelled as a result of precluding casual income was changed from two fortnights to four, and the period beyond which payment cannot be reinstated (after such a cancellation) without a new claim being lodged was changed from three fortnights to five. This is a fix-up. Changes to the Guide were not done at the time.</p>
<h2>Update 942G # Date 12 June 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Activity test. See guidelines 12.3100 to 12.3206.</p>
<p>With this amendment, three actions have been included as activity test breaches:</p>
<ul><li>failing to attend a job interview;</li>
<li>voluntary cessation or dismissal for misconduct from a labour market program; and</li>
<li>refusing/failing to provide or knowingly/recklessly providing false information of remunerative income.</li>
</ul><p>Also, the onus has been placed on the customer to show the delegate that sufficient reason exists for their voluntary unemployment or refusal of a job offer. The requirements will remove some of the discretion which now exists which will result in more consistent decisions across the network.</p>
