<h2>Update 839G # Date 20 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 30 - INCOME: ASSESSMENT FROM FINANCIAL ASSETS - Extended deeming. See guideline 30.3800 to 30.3808.</p>
<p>Advice to network that further information on shareholdings that cannot be located on SIV is available through 'Investment Help and Information' on the Retirement Programs Forum Bulletin Board.</p>
<h2>Update 838G # Date 20 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Rewrite of chapter 45, part B - activity test. See guidelines 1) 45.2000 to 45.2202, 2) 45.2300 to 45.2526 and 3) 45.2600 to 45.2905.</p>
<p>1) Part B has been amended to bring it in line with chapter 12, Part B - Activity Test (newstart allowance).</p>
<p>2) Part B has been amended to provide more relevant information on approved activities and to bring it in line with the activity test section for newstart allowance.</p>
<p>3) Part B has been amended to update the policy on the methods of monitoring a customers job search efforts and to bring it in line with the activity test section for newstart allowance. Policy on activity test breaches has also been included in Part B.</p>
<h2>Update 837G # Date 20 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 28 - ASSETS - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - How to assess the value of loans to companies and trusts. See guidelines 28.1610 to 28.1625.</p>
<p>Loans to companies and trusts are generally nor irrecoverable unless legal recovery action has proved the debtor's inability to repay.</p>
<h2 id="6march1997">Update 836G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 32 - INCOME AND ASSETS - DEPRIVATION - Reversal of gifting of assets. See guidelines 32.100 to 32.102.</p>
<p>The asset deprivation amount is maintained for five years regardless of whether the asset is later returned.</p>
<h2>Update 835G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Portability restriction for additional family payment for children of pensioners. See guidelines 42.320 to 42.323.</p>
<p>References to additional child payment have been changed to overseas child payment to reflect terminology used in the Income Security System. Cross references have been corrected.</p>
<h2>Update 834G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Pre-departure arrangements - departure interview. See guideline 42.418.</p>
<p>Cross references have been changed. References to additional child payment have been changed to overseas child payment to reflect terminology used in the Income Security System and study overseas has been amended to secondary study overseas.</p>
<h2>Update 833G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Payment of overseas child payment to pensioners overseas. See guidelines 17.5180 to 17.5185.</p>
<p>References to additional child payment have been changed to overseas child payment to reflect terminology used in the Income Security System. Corrections have been made to clarify who is entitled to receive overseas child payment.</p>
<h2>Update 832G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Clarification of foreign income. See guideline 17.7694.</p>
<p>Clarification that an overseas pension or benefit may be assessed as foreign income under the family payment income test.</p>
<h2>Update 831G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Definition of insufficient livelihood. See guidelines 15.1000 to 15.1004 (15.1005 has been deleted).</p>
<p>Clarifying how to determine placing themself in hardship.</p>
<h2>Update 830G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - (1) Education leaver - no dependents and under 18 years. (2) Victims of disasters - localised disasters. See guidelines 15.3010 and 15.3410 to 15.3414.</p>
<p>(1) Simplifies an obscure guideline, and changes an incorrect guideline reference.</p>
<p>(2) Deletes information that is repeated in the following segment and simplifies existing information about payment of special benefit due to acute hardship to victims of localised disasters.</p>
<h2>Update 829G # Date 6 March 1997</h2>
